                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> It would just be another thing that made the game slow & a pain in the ass. Sitting around medding for long periods of time != fun. It's not like it doesn't cost mana to tap the eyes..and it's not like I don't have to buy a good bit of stalking probes. If you don't have beads you are dependant on another player for them, which in turn helps that player out when you buy their items.<br /><br />This would be a very bad change. If they want to focus on necros, why not focus on fixing WoT, or CoB, or the still broken pathing, or the many broken and bugged events, the list of things goes on and on. And like someone said..it's not like we're the only class who benefits from things in a perfect world they wouldn't. Mage canni is actually amazingly efficient; they chain nuke for a fight, canni down during pull, and are pretty much FM by the time the next mob is in camp. With suspend minion they lose zero DPS.<br /><br />Anyway I understand the "it's not class defining" argument; neither are mod rods for mages..or click sticks for clerics..or fungi tunics on shammies..they just make the game not quite as painfully slow in a few situations. They've focused on making gameplay less tedious - this would make it -much- more tedious for the necro population.<br /><br />And that, is that.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
