                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I find it funny that people claim that equipment, in this case the probes/beads, are not part of the class balance.<br /><br />In that case, why don't you just take off all your equipment and play the class as it's supposed to be played - naked?<br /><br />Why don't you tell your warrior friend to take off all his armor and tank mobs naked?<br /><br />Why don't you tell your mage friend to stop using his epic pet, or your shaman friend to stop clicking his epic DoT?<br /><br />The fact of the matter is the equipment SoE decides to put into the game has EVERYTHING to do with class balance.  Spells are nothing more than extended forms of equipment for casters.  If you were a melee, or ever played a melee class, you would understand that Itemization = Balance for classes.  If they gave a 20/20 dagger to rogues that was available from a vendor, rogues would be overpowered.  By the same token, if rogues had nothing but 10/20 daggers dropping from the Plane of Time, no one would play a rogue cause they'd completely suck.<br /><br />Now, if the eyes were only available to necros with the beads, then yes I can understand how it'd not be part of necro balance.  However, since any one can get probes to mimick the effect and they're just as useful, I'd say it is as much part of necro class balance as the pre-nerfed CoS is - or even moreso, since the pre-nerfed CoS is simply irreplaceable by something as cheap as stalking probes.<br /><br />Saying that the inability to tap eyes is not a harmful nerf to the necro class is idiotic, because it assumes a difference between equipment and principle class skills, and that just isn't true in EQ.  EQ is not Diablo II and you get very few things free.  Not spells, not items, and not focus effects.  The nerf to eyes is as much of a nerf as if they made every form of mana preservation focus no longer work on DoTs - if that happened, there would be a simple uproar in many communities, but by the same token, it's a focus effect available on ITEMS, and as such shouldn't be considered a nerf to DoT classes, right?<br /><br />Wrong.<br /><br />If this goes live, the necro class will have been nerfed.  Be happy if you want to be, but who knows where the nerf stick will strike next? <br /> <br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="bottom"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Etadanik the Redeemed</span></font></td>
