se, my Two-Handed stats-o-crap stick with the 13.5 second cast time which will replace two of my most important slots with mostly-mundane wood, is much better that being able to cast and tap Eyes from my inventory slots. 13.5 seconds, 2HB man!!<br /><br />SoS + SK will keep you in mana and hps AS LONG as theres a supply of mobs to fight so no need to use the VP stick. With a lack of mobs prior to a big pull, or  when about to die, cursed after a boss, the VP stick is useless. When CAN you use the VP stick then? My only answer is fighting mana-draining mobs like PoFs ArchMagi where at least youre still doing something once your juice runs dry.<br /><br /><br />WTF people?.I am getting the impression that a number of NECs here actually dont care about this nerf because they havent used these tactics, or in at least a few cases have NO CLUE what theyre all about.<br /><br />Maybe next time it'll be Root for Root-Rotters, or agro for Agro-Kiting. This IS a nerf for Necromancers. Even IF it's a tactic you don't happen to use. <br /><br />Yes, if youre using KEI, tapping eyes WONT impact your ability to solo.<br /><br /><br />-Morloc<br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
